<item>
            <title>[SPARK-8414] Ensure ContextCleaner actually triggers clean ups</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-8414</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now it cleans up old references only through natural GCs, which may not occur if the driver has infinite RAM. We should do a periodic GC to make sure that we actually do clean things up. Something like once per 30 minutes seems relatively inexpensive.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
